 see   Dunsworth  ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":75,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":84,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":119,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Amabilia Davenport was born in 1140, in Cheshire, England. She had at least 1 son with William of Kinderton de Venables."},"et":{"1140–":"1140–Surnud","1135–1228":"1135–1228","1191–1249":"1191–1249","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1228":"1228","1249":"1249","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","1140":"1140","1191":"1191","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Kinderton cum Hulme, Cheshire, England":"Kinderton cum Hulme, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"1140–":"1140–Kuollut","1135–1228":"1135–1228","1191–1249":"1191–1249","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","1228":"1228","1249":"1249","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","1140":"1140","1191":"1191","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Kinderton cum Hulme, Cheshire, England"